<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Loan Prediction Result</title>
  <style>
    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      background-color: #f2f2f2;
      padding: 20px;
    }

    h1 {
      text-align: center;
    }

    .result {
      max-width: 400px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: #fff;
      border-radius: 5px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    }

    .approval {
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 24px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .approval.approved {
      color: #4CAF50;
    }

    .approval.not-approved {
      color: #f44336;
    }

    p {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Loan Prediction Result</h1>
  <div class="result">
    <p class="approval <%= prediction === 1 ? 'approved' : 'not-approved' %>">
      <%= prediction === 1 ? 'Approved' : 'Not Approved' %>
    </p>
  </div>
  <p>This project demonstrates a loan prediction model that predicts whether a loan application will be approved or not based on various parameters. The prediction result is displayed above.</p>
</body>
</html>
